c WD. Moreover, the similarity of the UV and X-ray fluxes, as\nwell as the approximate constancy of the hardness ratio within the BAT band,\nindicate that the boundary layer of the accretion disk remained optically thin\nto its own radiation throughout the brightening event, during which the rate of\naccretion onto the WD increased to 6.7 $\\times$ 10-9 Msun yr^{-1} (d/2 kpc)^2.\n(Abridged abstract version)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 8 Jan 2018 15:21:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 10 Sep 2018 17:13:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-11"}
